<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0861 </DOCNO><TEXT>Considerable progress has been made in developing techniques for the revegetationof acidic tailings and of rock wastes generated by coal and metal mining.This paper briefly reviews and discusses some of the problem areas whichare still unresolved for tailings and waste rock dumps in the metal miningindustry. Caution is expressed in extrapolating reclamation knowledgeapplicable to acidic coal spoils to acid tailings. Particularly in chemicalcharacterization of tailings and treatments to prevent pyrite oxidation.The status of rock waste vegetation is also briefly considered.</TEXT></DOC>